description:
When the gods change their plans for man's world, it's up to Wonder Woman to protect humanity against an invading army of male warriors and a new adversary called Genocide. An army of Olympians has risen for an all-out assault on war across the globe and only Wonder Woman can stop them in this new title collecting issues #20-27! One particular attack could spell the end of the Department of Metahuman Affairs and end WW's secret identity of Diana Prince. And Wonder Woman's life is changed forever when she faces a monster named Genocide who goes toe-to-toe with her . . . and wins.

Wonder Woman

Diana waging a fight against an aroused powerful Minotaur. The Minotauro said it is necessary, since their species is endangered. Diana says that the ends do not justify the means. The Minotaur can not save its species to kill humans. Diana defeats the Minotaur.

Watching Wonder Woman, is a group of fighting men. One of them said: Hippolyta`s daughter has years to change the world. Our fate Can not be left to Wonder Woman and the amazons. Changing the World is not a job for women. It `s the job for men". However the Olympians are back to earth. Hippolyta provides that hard times are approaching.

However, in the department of metahumans affairs, the agent prince gives instructions for a target human disturbance at the twin rivers mall downtown. After a misunderstanding with the Steel (the Director), Officer Prince and other agents go by helicopter to Two Rivers. A target man is killing all the innocent people of the place, Wonder Woman attacks the creature. But attacks against the creature with a powerful blow. The creature picks up an innocent and to Wonder Woman asks to surrender. Wonder Woman does not give up and attacks Genocide. Genocide attacked Diana with powerful strokes. Genocide leaves Wonder Woman seriously injured in the rubble (Genocide steals the Lasso of Truth from Diana). Meanwhile Tom and anothers arrived on the zone.

However Tom frees Wonder Woman. Zeus calls the various Amazons back to Themyscira. Dona Troy and arrives on the scene are shocked about what happened to Diana. Dona decides to take Diana back to Themyscira. However Genocide continues its bloody persecution (Genocide kills all the innocents by the way). Several members of the Justice League of America (John Stewart, Tornado, Black and Black Africa Cannary), Genocide without powder or mercy attacks the Green Lantern John Stwerart. Wonder Woman is recovering from serious injuries with Tom and she is very concerned that the magic lasso is very dangerous in the wrong hands. Wonder Woman decides to attack Genocide (Woman draws its golden armor). Tom objected to, but Wonder Woman will go with a group of brave warriors hunt Genocide (a group formed in addition to Diana, Dona Troy, Cassie and Gorilla Knights). Genocide attacks Black Cannary but Wonder Woman and her group arrived on zone. Wonder Woman attacks Genocide with an ax.

An army of Olympians has risen for an all-out assault on war across the globe and only Wonder Woman can stop them in this new title collecting issues #26-33! One particular attack could spell the end of the Department of Metahuman Affairs and end WW's secret identity of Diana Prince. And Wonder Woman's life is changed forever when she faces a monster named Genocide who goes toe-to-toe with her . . . and wins.
name: TPB/HC

volume.name: Wonder Woman: Rise of the Olympian

description: Disturbing visions plucked from the malignant mind of Norman Osborn lead the intrepid Agents to the darkest depths of the Atlantic Ocean, where Namora must have words with her infamous cousin - the Sub-Mariner! Then, The Agents of Atlas find themselves racing around the world to rescue their leader! Jimmy Woo and M-11 find themselves under the talons of the most terrible power in China...the deadly- and beautiful- JADE CLAW! Plus: the Atomic Age heroes meet the original gamma ray giant and learn the meaning of HULK SMASH!!! Collecting AGENTS OF ATLAS #6-11.
name: TPB

description: The net is closing in. The FBI is against the CIA, the CIA is against Candyman, Mister No is against everyone. Phil Mulligan is able to find the proof to clear Darlene’s son, Leo. But the deus ex machina of the matter is the “living dead”, Evans!
name: Nel Centro del Mirino

description: The CIA agent Hiden forces Mister No to leave the United States, just a few months before Mister No’s father is due to be released from the Prison on Rykers island. What secrets does Mister Drake hide? Mister No’s return to Manaus is far from happy: his friends Esse-Esse, Paulo Adolfo, Clara and Isabela have disappeared…
name: Manaus!

description: Esse-Esse is suspected of the murder of a rich Fazendeiro’s son, Senhor Marquao. Marquao’s men attempt to kill the German: Esse-Esse’s days are numbered and Mister No gets himself employed by Marquao to find the culprit. The Fazenda is swarming with different kinds of people, many of whom are hiding a secret. Which of them is the assassin?
name: Intrighi e Veleni

description: A group of Americans (a doctor and three marines) come to Manaus to bring medicine to Father Lepke’s mission. Mister No is hired as guide, as the mission is in an unknown part of the forest. But, unknown to Jerry…
name: Acque Pericolose

description: Never trust your clients, Mister No! The Americans to whom he was acting as a guide are really gangsters paid by the godfather Machiavelli. They are looking for Father Norton, a one-time criminal who used to work for the crime boss, to make him pay for his betrayal. And all hell has broken out in Father Lepke’s mission!
name: L'Ora della Violenza

description: In Paraguay, in Venezuela, Mister No is forced by the corrupt local authorities to be the pilot for Norton, an executive of a powerful petrol company. But some terrorists blow up an oil well in Santa Elena de Uairen. To put out the fire, they have to transport nitro-glycerine by truck to the flaming well. Mister No leads the suicide expedition!
name: Uomini Senza Speranza

description: The road to Santa Elena de Uairen is long and particularly winding and rough and the nitro-glycerine risks exploding, thereby condemning all those who are transporting it to death. Enemies become friends (Ezquerra), others reveal a dramatic past (Kelly). And the terrorists are waiting for our men, together with an unexpected adversary…
name: Missione Suicida

description: Mister No has new, unusual clients: an entomologist who deals with lepidopters, one who studies Amazonian ants and a attractive expert in arachnids. But all three seem to be hiding something and they are extremely skillful in the use of fire arms….What is their secret?
name: La Foresta dei Misteri

description: Mister No is guiding two men of the cloth, Father Albarn and the young Ignacio Ponzalo, to the São José mission. Ignacio hopes to find his cousin Gabriel, captured fourteen years before by the Manbicuara Indios, who slaughtered his parents. He does finds him, but two shady individuals, the hunter Ruiz and Moraes, want to capture the white Indio….
name: L'Indio Bianco

description: Ruiz and Moraes have killed some of the Manbicuaras, who take out their anger on the innocent missionaries and Mister No. Terror is rife in São José, but young Gabriel likes Jerry’s jacket and this saves his life. When Mister No discovers the identity of his true enemy, he has a real surprise…
name: Sangue di Guerriero

description: Three men gifted with extra-sensory faculties (Revok, Hockey and Glaeken) escape from the institution where they were held under strict observation, and make their way to Amazonia. One of them, Glaeken, hires Mister No to take him to a ghostly house in the jungle, Villa Cabral, the scene of one of his most extraordinary adventures…
name: Il Potere della Mente

description: The man with the third eye -as the natives have dubbed him - is called Daryl Revok and, with his esp faculties, he has subdued the Makú Indio tribe. Mister No and Glaeken definitely have to stop him: if he possesses the Yehalla, the spirit of revenge, Revok will become a god and terror will reign on earth!
name: La Stirpe dei Dannati

description: From the first, he was a fighter. When the spaceship that exiled the Hulk to Sakaar exploded, it killed his queen and ravaged his kingdom. The Hulk returned to Earth to seek revenge, but he left behind a child he thought had died with its mother. Instead, the boy survived - hatching in a lake a fire, and growing strong and savage to match the world around him. Skaar, son of Hulk, possesses his father's size and strength, and more than his share of rage. The refugees of Sakaar have found hope in this. Theirs is a dangerous planet, but they have a new champion to protect them. And their world will never be the same again. Collecting SKAAR: SON OF HULK #1-6, SAVAGE WORLD OF SAKAAR and material from HULK FAMILY.
name: HC/TPB

description: This special issue centers on masked comic book heroes who also appeared in the movie serials!! Golden Age comic stories include Spy Smasher by Emil Gershwin, Captain Midnight in “The Cross-Country Crime”, drawn by Dan Barry and taken from his Fawcett comic series, from issue #57 of his own book, circa 1947. There’s also Harry “A” Chesler’s Rocketman, in an untitled story drawn by Tony Cataldo, ans a new “retro” story starring The Black Commando, hero of the Columbia chapter play, The Secret Code. It’s called “Hitler’s Mechanical Monster”, and is written and drawn by Bill Black. Also, indepth articles on the serials themselves, including Captain America and King Of The Rocketmen from Republic Pictures, and Batman & Robin and Captain Midnight. Lots of photos, poster and ad reproductions. Color cover, interiors are black and white with graytones. 52-page standard comic book format.
name: Spy Smasher Vs. American Smasher

description: After recent cataclysmic events, the Son of Hulk is abandoned, wandering aimless and alone. Can he find his way in the savage, hopeless universe that promises only his destruction? And have any of his allies survived to stand by his side. Join us as Paul Jenkins (WOLVERINE: ORIGIN, INCREDIBLE HULK) takes the reigns for this surprising new story! Collecting SKAAR: SON OF HULK #13-17.
name: HC

volume.name: Hulk: Son of Hulk - Dark Son Rising

description: Special salute to the original Holyoke Comics Cat-Man! This issue contains the never before reprinted secret origin of The Cat-Man and Kitten, taken from Cat-Man Comics # 27, and stunningly rendered by Bob Fujitani. It also guest-stars The Deacon and Mickey- a Golden Age crossover!! The beautiful and buxom Phantom Lady battles “Satan”s Seal”, from the #5 issue of her 1954 Ajax/Farrel series; and the awesome Nedor champion The Black Terror busts up “The Model Crimes”, in a Mort Meskin?Jerry Robinson story from Exciting Comics #64. Another import fills out the bill, as the Australian version of The Cat-Man romps through a 21-page adventure from the Frew Publication’s series 21st issue from the late 1950′s. It is illustrated by the talented John Dixon, and is titled “The Electronic Monster!” Once more this title packs vintage
name: The Story of Rosetta!

description: During the Golden Age of comics, Everett M. Arnold’s “Quality Comics” was aptly named, as he hired nothing but the very best artists in the industry to illustrate his features. We’ve spotlighted the creme de la creme among them here. This issue starts out with Espionage-Starring The Black X, from Smash Comics, a pre-Spirit gem by the great Will Eisner, followed by Stuart Taylor- Strange Stories of The Supernatural, (Not actually a Quality feature, rather a Fiction House strip from an early issue of Jumbo Comics ) a sci-fi adventure drawn by the incomparable Lou Fine; a pair of vintage Fox Features strips, both out of an early issue of Wonderworld Comics: Dr Fung, by Bob Powell, and more Eisner magic on Yarko The Great. The legendary Jack Cole clocks in with the wacky origin of The Death Patrol from Military Comics #1, and an homage/restoration of Paul Gustavson’s Human Bomb, (the origin story) done by none other than C. C. Beck. Also, “The Collector’s Corner” by Bill Black focuses on DC Comics’ The Flash this issue. And if that’s not enough, as a special feature, we have part 1 of an interview with the man who knew and worked with them all… one-time Quality Comics art director (and Blackhawk co-creator) Chuck Cuidera!! Color cover, interiors are black and white with graytones. 52-page standard comic book format.
name: Devil's Island

description:
Commando - a group of British Land personnel, highly-trained in unconventional warfare. Very dangerous opponents.

Kommando - a unit of South African irregular troops, highly-trained in unconventional warfare.

Commando versus Kommando - a no-holds barred battle whose outcome could tip the balance of the Second World War.
name: Commando versus Kommando

description:
Two generals - one British, one German - were being held to ransom by Italian bandits. Both sides had decided to pay up, but there was a lot of nasty double-dealing going on.

Any rescue team would find itself on an impossible mission, and that was very bad news for both generals!
name: Rescue Team

description:
Feldjagerkorps was its name - the new group formed to maintain order among the demoralised troops as the Nazi war machine, broken by cruel Russian winters and the Red Army, retreated in disarray.

Kurt Hensel, veteran of the Eastern Front, was one of the original members of this elite corps. This is his story...
name: The Final Hours

description:
Lieutenant Alec Paton was not a happy man when he was put in charge of a Royal Navy gun crew on an armed Dutch freighter. It was skippered by Captain Paul Grootemann who seethed with bitter hatred for the Germans who had killed his son.

Neither had much respect for the other and when they were ordered to sail for Hong Kong, both felt they were in the wrong place fighting the wrong war.

Then they tangled with the Japs and, in the heat of the Pacific where cool heads and calm decisions were called for, no one on board the rusty old freighter was found wanting.
name: The Wrong War

description: Sporting a never-before-printed cover of Magazine Enterprises’ The Avenger by Dick Ayers, M. E.’s cold-war crimefighter is in the lead spot with a reprint of “Death Has Three Faces” from The Avenger #1,with art by Dick Ayers. Another ’50′s favorite returns, Sterling’s Captain Flash, by Mike Sekowsky in “Man Or Myth”, from Captain Flash #4. Mr. Scarlet solves “The Case Of The Impregnasble Vault”, drawn by Carl Pfeufer, for Fawcett Comics’ Wow #50, and Street and Smith’s Rex King, Adventurer teams up with his pet panther Kato to keep the African jungles crime-free in an adventure drawn by Al Plastino for Super Magician #2, circa 1941. Then, one of the most memorable clashes of the Golden Age is revisited as we see New Friday’s Daredevil Vs. The Claw, in a line-for-line recreation of Jack Cole’s masterpiece, executed by comics legend C.C. Beck. Also, part 2 of the interview with Quality Comics great Chuck Cuidera, and The Collector’s Corner by former Mad Magazine editor, Jerry DeFuccio. Another fat volume chock full of vintage comics action and fun from the 1940′s and ’50′s. Color cover, interiors are black and white with graytones. 52-page standard comic book format.
name: Death Has Three Faces

volume.name: Nine Lives of Felix the Cat

name: Bugs Bunny & Co.: Svelato il Segreto di Taddeo!
